properties.Venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
properties.Address:
This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
Los Angeles, CA 90015
properties.Description:
Thanks for signing up to attend this Text Banking Event! Yang Gang does not have enough volunteers in Iowa, so we must volunteer digitally to connect with voters. Iowa is an essential state that we must outreach. Our concentration will be rural Iowa.

Below is what we plan to do:
* Immediately send Voter Identification texts to thousands of potential voters
* Get trained to text if you haven’t already gone through the training process.
* If you can, follow this step-by-step guide to get trained prior to the event: http://bit.ly/35Qhi9Q

Note:
Sorry, this space is NOT "child" friendly. No one will be admitted under the age of 17! No exceptions.

This is a private business that is offering office space for Yang Gang text banking. The max capacity is 12 people at a time. You do not have to stay for the full hours of this event, but the minimum hours of volunteering that's expected is 2.

Feel free to bring a potluck of food and drinks to share. There are also local restaurants on the ground floor of this building.

properties.Title: Primary Conversation w/ the NH Yang Gang
properties.Description:
A part of the Riverwalk Cafe's series of informal campaign conversations, we're excited to be talking to supporters and neighbors alike on Thursday, January 16. The goal of this series is to offer you the opportunity to engage in some civic discourse to learn more about the candidates on the NH ballot, and more specifically hear from the team members that make up each campaign.

You'll have the opportunity to connect with Andrew Yang's NH campaign team and ask questions about the issues that matter most to you.

The Riverwalk Cafe offers a number of deals - so stop in, grab a drink and bite to eat, participate in and join us for a conversation about the primary.

properties.Description:
Signature Collecting at the Holiday Randolph Street Market!

The holiday event at the Randolph street market is one of the most popular things to do in Chicago around this time of year. The market is open monthly and is generally popular all year. While it is indoors during the winter, the venue is massive and people come from all over the state to attend. People who are interested in supporting local businesses, unique vendors and holiday shopping will be there.

I STRONGLY recommend finding a high traffic spot in a public area near the entrance to collect signatures for Andrew Yang. Please review the Illinois Signature Collection Guide here: http://bit.ly/ILSignatureCollectionGuide

Note: If you would like to start collecting signatures prior to the event, check out the signature guide! No need to wait for an event to get started. Farmer's markets, BMVs, movie theaters, libraries, concerts are all good options. #SecureTheBag #HumanityFirst

properties.Title: Iowa Phone Bank Training
properties.Description:
With less than 80 days until caucus, we need all hands on deck. If you live in Iowa and want to make a huge difference, we need more volunteers. This is one of the best ways you can reach out to your neighbors and move the needle!

This training is to teach you the basics of Phone Banking and get you in touch with a Staff Organize that can get you an effective list to call to get the candidates name out there! The training lasts for about an hour, just select a time slot that works best for you. On the call, you're able to do a few practice phone calls with an Organizer on the line to help if you get stuck.

Remember we rely on this grassroots effort that you helped create, but we can't just stop at vocalizing support. We have to put in more effort than any other campaign out there, and this is where it all starts!
